<h1>Problem 1717 - 2011 IMOSL, N2, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Consider a polynomial \(P(x) = (x + d_1)(x + d_2) \cdot \dots \cdot (x + d_9)\), where \(d_1, d_2, \dots , d_9\) are nine distinct integers. Prove that there exists an integer \(N\) such that for all integers \(x \ge N\) the number \(P(x)\) is divisible by a prime number greater than \(20\).</p>
